    • Method Detail

      • getAgencyPromiseItems

        java.util.List<AgencyPromiseItem> getAgencyPromiseItems()
        The data model is set up such that AgencyCycleDist (the super class of AgencyCyclePayment) has an array of AgencyDistItem elements (the superclass of AgencyPaymentItem). This method just gets all the elements out of the AgencyDistItems array and casts each one to AgencyPromiseItem and puts them all in a list and returns it.
        Returns:
        list of all AgencyPromiseItem elements on this payment

        Execute this promise as agency cycle payment
        Parameters:
        paymentReceipt - NewAgencyMoneyDetails containing the information about the details of this Payment
        writeoffDifferent - If true the method will writeoff the different between the net amount of the promise and that of the InvoiceItems net owed

      • isActive

        boolean isActive()
        Returns:
        true if the promise has been executed, is not reversed, and is not currently applied to a payment, though it will return true on promises that have been applied to a payment, but the payment was reversed.

      • apply

        @Deprecated
void apply(AgencyCyclePayment paymentApplyingTo)
        Deprecated. (Since 8.0.0) Executing the payment that was created from this promise will apply this promise. You are no longer allowed to apply a promise except by executing the attached payment. Use AgencyBillPaymentMoneySetup.setAppliedFromPromise(AgencyCyclePromise) after using AgencyBillMoneySetupFactory to instantiate a Payment Money Setup, and then execute the payment.
        Pay this promise eg. when execute this promise as payment of make a payment from this promise then excecute the payment. After this, the promise will be inactive.
        Parameters:
        paymentApplyingTo - AgencyCyclePayment you are applying this Promise to

      • payFromSuspenseItems

        AgencyCyclePromise payFromSuspenseItems(BaseSuspDistItem[] suspPmntItems,
                                      InvoiceItem[] invoiceItems,
                                      AgencyCycleDistPrefill prefill,
                                      DistItemDisposition disposition,
                                      Bundle bundle)
        CC-47324, continuation of CC-45513: Release the suspense payment items, and then create a new Modifying Promise with new agency promise items to pay each of the statement items with the given prefill options. All the suspense payment items have to belong to the current agency promise.
        Parameters:
        suspPmntItems - The Suspense Payment Items we are going to release in order to get the funds to pay the statement items. Cannot be empty
        invoiceItems - The invoice items we wish to pay from the funds in the suspense items. Cannot be empty
        prefill - pre-fill option for how we want to pay the statement items
        disposition - what should be done with the items, e.g., carry forward, write-off, etc.
        bundle - The bundle to create the AgencyCyclePayment in @return the (unexecuted) modifying promise with the new dist items for the given statment items added.
        Returns:
        New modifying Agency Promise using suspense items as promise items.

      • isApplied

        boolean isApplied()
        Returns:
        true if the promise has been applied as a payment, otherwise false.
